Algorithm to Calculate the Sum of Even Numbers:
1.Start.
2.Input the value of n from the user.
3.Initialize sum = 0.
Use a loop to iterate from 1 to n:
Check if the current number is even (number % 2 == 0).
If it is, add the number to sum.
After the loop ends, print the value of sum.
Stop

PSEUDOCODE:
START
    INPUT n
    sum ← 0
    FOR i FROM 1 TO n DO
        IF i MOD 2 = 0 THEN
            sum ← sum + i
        ENDIF
    ENDFOR
    PRINT sum
END

FLOWCHART:
A[Start] --> B[Input n]
    B --> C[Initialize sum = 0]
    C --> D[Set i = 1]
    D --> E{Is i <= n?}
    E -->|Yes| F{Is i even?}
    F -->|Yes| G[Add i to sum]
    F -->|No| H[Increment i by 1]
    G --> H
    H --> E
    E -->|No| I[Output sum]
    I --> J[Stop]
